	<title>Rotations are Distance Preserving</title>
	<caption>Rotations are Distance Preserving</caption>
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>We say that a linear transformation <latex>L</latex> preserves the distance between two points <latex>\Vect{a}</latex>  and <latex>\Vect{b}</latex> if the distance from <latex>\Vect{a}</latex> to <latex>\Vect{b}</latex> is equal to the distance from <latex>L(\Vect{a})</latex> to <latex>L(\Vect{b})</latex>. For example, a rotation of the plane about the origin preserves the distance between any two points.</para>
			
			
